			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">FrankenGraphics wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">A mapper that is simple enough to be about as cheap as nrom, unrom, gtrom etc, yet passively interleaves rows from two nametables, would nicely fill a role for any homebrew that seeks a slanted topdown perspective (popular with adventure games, rpgs, action puzzles) or an isometric view.<br />[...]<br />I'm not well-read on the cartridge port side, but am i right to believe all it'd take is cutting and jumpwiring some traces? alternatively from a design perspective, inculde a three-point jumper/solder bridge to be able to reroute the behaviour.<br /></div>Yes, one could easily add cartridge hardware—in fact, just a 74'161—to automatically interleave namatables every 4 rows.<br /><br />Specifically: latch PPU A2..0 on reads from pattern tables (i.e. 74'161.CK ← PPU/RD and 74'161.LE ← PPUA13). Because of how the PPU's fetch cadence works, the first fetch will have bogus results—that nametable fetch follows a sprite pattern fetch instead of a background pattern fetch—but that can be concealed with the &quot;mask left 8 pixels&quot; control.<br /><br />The complicated part is if you ever want to turn it off.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
