						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Specifically: latch PPU A2..0 on reads from pattern tables (i.e. 74'161.CK ← PPU/RD and 74'161.LE ← PPUA13).</div><br />OK, I'm trying to make sense of if this: why do I need to latch PPU A2..0, and what do I do with them?<br /><br />Now that I think of it, couldn't I latch just A2 (the bit that selects the top or bottom 4 rows of a tile) on pattern table reads, and use that as the lower name table selection bit? I'm not very good with hardware, so sorry if I'm way off, but my thinking is that whenever the top half of a tile is read, the left name table will be selected, and whenever the bottom half of a tile is read, the right name table will be selected. Does that make any sense?</div>

